--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. INTRODUCTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Mizar is a GPLV3 software which renders realistic skies in real time
 with WebGL. It is available for all platforms.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Just run "java -jar MIZAR-1.0-install.jar"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. REQUIREMENTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 JAVA 1.6 or higher
 A graphical card compatible with WebGL.
 Compatible browsers : Chrome, Firefox, Safari

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. QUICK START
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 To run MIZAR on Windows, please :
 use the shortcut if available or click on @INSTALL_PATH@/mizar.bat


 To run MIZAR on Unix, please :
 use the shortcut if available or run @INSTALL_PATH@/mizar.sh start

 Then connect yourself on http://@HOST_NAME@:8182/sitools/mizar/app

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6. THANKS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This software is based on technology developed by :

  - GlobWeb (https://github.com/TPZF/GlobWeb) for rendering, developed by TPZF SSA.
  - Portions of the code related to Healpix and coordinates system transformation have been traduced in JavaScript from Healpix library (http://sourceforge.net/projects/healpix/)
  - The FITS library (http://astrojs.github.io/fitsjs/) for loading FITS file, developed by Amit Kapadia.
  - The SAMP library (http://astrojs.github.io/sampjs/) for using the SAMP Web Profile from within web pages, developed by Amit Kapadia.
  - The WCS library (http://astrojs.github.io/wcsjs/) for computing fits files coordinates on the sky, developed by Amit Kapadia
  - The GZip library (http://github.com/beatgammit/gzip-js) for uncompressing g-zipped fits files, developed by Jameson Little.
  - ColorMap have been traduced in JavaScript from Aladin Sky Atlas (http://aladin.u-strasbg.fr/aladin.gml), developed by CDS.
  - Multi Order Coverage library (http://wiki.ivoa.net/twiki/bin/view/IVOA/MocInfo), developped by CDS 
  - Hierarchical Progressive Surveys, developed by CDS
  - Sesame name resolver service, developed by CDS
  - Reverse name resolver service, developed by CDS
  - Name resolver service for solar bodies, developed by IMCCE
  - Healpix library (http://sourceforge.net/projects/healpix/)
  - SITools2 framework (http://github.com/SITools2/), developed by CNES

This software is also based on external requirements, specified by :
    - Alexandre Beelen (IDOC)
    - Andre Schaaff (CDS)
